metadata.name: Enlightened Journey #237
metadata.description:
A digital journey through nature.

Made in p5js

Special thanks to @Zancan and @TenebrisVia for inspiring me to code with nature, along with the work of Linda Rous for inspiring the use of perspective and stairs in the scene. Also, thanks to the FX Hash and Twitter communities for the wonderful feedback and suggestions which helped throughout the design process.

metadata.name: Zaratan II #32
metadata.description:
As for the first Zaratan, the Generative Token chooses between three primitives (cubes, spheres, triangle stripes) and places it along a new kind of parametric curve with parameters varying with noise() function as source of smooth motion.

New shapes are added layer after layer with new forms and colors.

At any time the user can pause the generation by pressing 'p', resume it with 'r' and save a 1600x1600 png with 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- primitives choice (3)
- initial conditions
- shapes evolution
- colors evolution (only 10% will be bi-chromatic)


Press:
- 'p' to pause
- 'r' to resume
- 's' to save a 1600x1600 png image

metadata.name: FairyCells #268
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press Â«Â EÂ Â» to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022
